WEBVTT

00:01.131 --> 00:04.961
♪♪

00:07.224 --> 00:09.139
[annoyed] Honey?

00:09.270 --> 00:10.445
Do I hear the sound
of chicken bones

00:10.575 --> 00:11.924
approaching
the disposal?

00:12.055 --> 00:13.796
No, you hear the sound of

00:13.926 --> 00:16.799
chicken bones
being disposed of.

00:16.929 --> 00:17.930
[switch clicks,
disposal grinding]

00:18.061 --> 00:21.108
Oh?! You suddenly want
to help me clean up?!

00:21.238 --> 00:23.371
[grunts]

00:23.501 --> 00:25.025
You can't just
throw everything in there

00:25.155 --> 00:26.548
and expect it to disappear.

00:26.678 --> 00:28.115
It's not the ocean,
Francine.

00:28.245 --> 00:29.986
B-b-b-burned.

00:30.117 --> 00:31.683
Shut up, Klaus.
That wasn't even a burn.

00:31.814 --> 00:32.902
Yeah, Klaus.

00:33.033 --> 00:34.773
When I'm burned,
I'll let ya know.

00:34.904 --> 00:39.256
Okay, so no chicken
down the disposal,

00:39.387 --> 00:42.129
but how about fish?

00:42.259 --> 00:44.914
[chuckling] That --
That's funny.

00:45.045 --> 00:46.263
That's making me laugh.

00:46.394 --> 00:48.222
And I've decided to
join in the joke!

00:49.571 --> 00:51.399
-[frightened groans]
-Francine?

00:51.529 --> 00:53.140
-Hit the switch.
-[disposal whirring]

00:53.270 --> 00:54.402
Okay, we've all had our fun.

00:54.532 --> 00:56.012
Now put me down!

00:56.143 --> 00:57.709
If you insist...

00:57.840 --> 01:00.190
Stan, now you're making me
laugh.

01:00.321 --> 01:03.628
-And making me kind of hot.
-[shouts]

01:03.759 --> 01:05.587
[screaming] Oh, no!
Oohheeeghhagh! Help!

01:05.717 --> 01:07.850
[mockingly]
Oohheeeghhagh!

01:07.980 --> 01:09.243
That's you!

01:09.591 --> 01:12.072
I guess you canput chicken
down the drain.

01:12.202 --> 01:13.856
-[laughing derisively]
-[screams]

01:13.986 --> 01:16.206
It sounds like
everybody's having a good time.

01:16.337 --> 01:18.121
Yeah, Klaus is in the disposal!

01:18.252 --> 01:19.862
Tell that idiot
pieces of shit

01:19.992 --> 01:21.429
are supposed to go
in the toilet.

01:21.559 --> 01:25.346
[laughing]

01:25.476 --> 01:27.652
To the ice cream store!
My treat!

01:29.872 --> 01:32.092
Remember,
I'm a rum raisin guy.

01:32.222 --> 01:33.963
ROGER: Cool, I'll put some
in a waffle cone

01:34.094 --> 01:36.400
-and throw it in the trash.
-[laughter]

01:36.531 --> 01:39.229
FRANCINE:
Nowthat was a burn, fish.

01:39.360 --> 01:42.014
♪♪

01:42.145 --> 01:44.452
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.♪

01:44.582 --> 01:48.238
♪ I got a feelin' that it's gonna be a wonderful day
♪

01:48.369 --> 01:51.459
♪ The sun in the sky
has a smile on his face♪

01:51.589 --> 01:56.028
♪ And he's shinin' a salute
to the American race♪

01:57.856 --> 02:01.338
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say♪

02:01.469 --> 02:03.645
-♪ Good --♪
-♪ Good morning, U.S.A.♪

02:03.775 --> 02:04.776
Aah!

02:06.256 --> 02:09.259
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.♪

02:09.390 --> 02:13.437
♪♪

02:13.568 --> 02:16.136
Welp,
that was the last straw.

02:16.266 --> 02:18.138
I am leaving.

02:18.268 --> 02:20.183
It's too late
for apologies.

02:20.314 --> 02:22.359
Nothing
could make it right.

02:22.490 --> 02:25.145
Not even acknowledging
my existence in any way.

02:25.275 --> 02:27.451
Alright, Klaus.
What's all this?

02:27.582 --> 02:28.713
You -- You're
selling lemonade?

02:28.844 --> 02:30.411
No, I'm leaving.

02:30.541 --> 02:32.630
I've never asked for anything
but a little respect.

02:32.761 --> 02:35.111
And it's clear
I'm not going to get it.

02:35.242 --> 02:37.244
Okay, okay.
I'll buy a lemonade.

02:37.374 --> 02:40.072
[screams]
I'm not selling lemonade!

02:40.203 --> 02:41.683
I'm leaving! Forever!

02:41.813 --> 02:44.468
One day you'll all regret
how you treated me!

02:46.340 --> 02:49.169
-Should we stop him?
-The lemonade guy?

02:49.299 --> 02:51.258
He's just being dramatic.
He'll be back.

02:54.913 --> 02:58.090
Okay, kids.
Help Mom with the groceries.

02:58.221 --> 03:00.310
Jeff Junior,
you stop drawing

03:00.441 --> 03:02.443
rockets shooting lasers
on my windows.

03:02.573 --> 03:04.271
[phone beeps]

03:04.401 --> 03:07.665
Klaus died?
Klaus the fish?

03:07.796 --> 03:11.278
Geez, I haven't seen him
since he walked out.

03:11.408 --> 03:14.411
[Marvin Gaye's "I Heard It
Through The Grapevine"plays]

03:14.542 --> 03:17.719
♪♪

03:17.849 --> 03:22.289
♪ Ooh, I bet you're wonderin'
how I knew♪

03:22.419 --> 03:26.641
♪ 'Bout your plans
to make me blue♪

03:26.771 --> 03:30.210
♪ With some other guy
you knew before♪

03:30.340 --> 03:32.255
-♪ Between the two of us guys♪
-[phone rings]

03:32.386 --> 03:34.736
♪ You know
I loved you more♪

03:34.866 --> 03:38.957
♪ It took me
by surprise I must say♪

03:39.088 --> 03:42.744
♪ When I found out yesterday♪

03:42.874 --> 03:45.790
♪ Don't you know that I heard it through the grapevine
♪

03:45.921 --> 03:47.227
[phone rings]

03:47.357 --> 03:49.316
Go for the Stanimal.

03:49.446 --> 03:50.926
Oh, when?

03:51.056 --> 03:52.971
Yeah, I know
where Francine's house is.

03:53.102 --> 03:54.538
That's where
I used to sleep in my car

03:54.669 --> 03:57.106
until a judge and I
came to a mutual agreement

03:57.237 --> 03:58.673
that Francine
be rewarded that car

03:58.803 --> 04:01.153
and I remain 80 yards away
at all times.

04:03.678 --> 04:04.766
STAN: Hey!

04:04.896 --> 04:05.941
You know the deal.

04:06.071 --> 04:07.247
Neither of us gets to do it

04:07.377 --> 04:09.249
until I can afford
a second bullet.

04:11.686 --> 04:15.124
♪♪

04:15.255 --> 04:17.474
[doorbell rings]

04:17.605 --> 04:19.607
[whirring]

04:19.737 --> 04:22.479
Steve.
It's been years.

04:22.610 --> 04:23.741
Hello, Mother.

04:26.614 --> 04:29.486
I follow your company
on Newstagram.

04:29.617 --> 04:32.010
You just bought
freakin' Hawaii!

04:32.141 --> 04:33.708
As a place to store
my shoes.

04:33.838 --> 04:35.405
I'm doing quite well, yes.

04:35.536 --> 04:37.059
Is hehere?

04:37.189 --> 04:38.930
Of course he's here.

04:39.061 --> 04:40.584
He's my husband now.

04:40.715 --> 04:41.977
And he's yourfather.

04:42.107 --> 04:43.457
He is not my father.

04:43.587 --> 04:46.024
He's my ex-best friend.

04:46.155 --> 04:48.505
[speaking French]

04:48.636 --> 04:50.812
Toshi, you finally
learned another language...

04:50.942 --> 04:52.814
and you chose French?

04:52.944 --> 04:55.164
That's the kind of kissing
he does.

04:55.295 --> 04:56.513
[loudly kisses]

04:56.644 --> 04:58.863
Ooh, la, la.

04:58.994 --> 05:01.301
Croissant.

05:01.431 --> 05:02.302
[bam!]

05:02.432 --> 05:03.477
Hey, everyone.

05:03.607 --> 05:04.826
Papa Toshi.

05:04.956 --> 05:07.481
Whoa, you only had one kid
in your Christmas card.

05:07.611 --> 05:08.656
That was 10 years ago.

05:08.786 --> 05:10.440
I wish it were 15.

05:10.571 --> 05:12.529
You must be
the little darlings

05:12.660 --> 05:14.444
my daughter's
been keeping from me.

05:14.575 --> 05:16.490
As a good mother,
I try to shield them

05:16.620 --> 05:18.666
from drunk housewives
and bad haircuts.

05:19.841 --> 05:22.626
I hope you wike it.

05:22.757 --> 05:25.673
I puwled the skeweton out
awl by mysewf.

05:25.803 --> 05:27.327
JEFF: That's Noah.

05:27.457 --> 05:29.633
[quietly] We're a little worriedabout him.

05:29.764 --> 05:32.070
Has trouble
saying "L"'s.

05:32.201 --> 05:34.638
[rumbling]

05:34.769 --> 05:37.685
What up, sluts?
Happy Klaus's funeral.

05:37.815 --> 05:39.861
Roger! My floor!

05:39.991 --> 05:41.341
Cool, right?

05:41.471 --> 05:43.343
Above-ground traffic
is for poor people.

05:43.473 --> 05:45.257
I got here from Tokyo
in 20 minutes.

05:45.388 --> 05:46.433
Bored
right through the core.

05:46.563 --> 05:48.478
No poors in the core,
baby.

05:48.609 --> 05:51.916
[metallic rattling]

05:52.047 --> 05:53.875
Veela, why aren't you
stealing anything?

05:54.005 --> 05:57.226
Stan! How the hell
did you get in my house?!

05:57.357 --> 06:01.361
I, uh, still have
a key to the backdoor.

06:03.798 --> 06:05.365
Dad, it's good to...

06:07.062 --> 06:08.106
Y-You look...

06:08.237 --> 06:09.325
Alive.

06:09.456 --> 06:10.805
Oh, you noticed?

06:10.935 --> 06:11.849
Sorry I'm late, gang.

06:11.980 --> 06:13.590
I was busy being awesome,

06:13.721 --> 06:16.332
eating really expensive cookies
whenever I want,

06:16.463 --> 06:19.509
swimming in all the oceans,
and not having any parasites.

06:19.640 --> 06:21.163
[silverware clatters]

06:21.293 --> 06:24.122
Well, I'm sure
you'd all like to unpack.

06:24.253 --> 06:26.255
Hayley,
you take your old room.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.692
Steve, you share the attic
with Roger.

06:28.823 --> 06:32.740
Toshi and I turned your bedroom
into an ass-blast-itorium.

06:32.870 --> 06:34.524
[chuckles derisively]
Real creative.

06:34.655 --> 06:38.615
Hey, don't turn my kitchen
into a sass-back-itorium!

06:38.746 --> 06:40.312
Stan, there's a blanket
in the basement.

06:40.443 --> 06:41.705
Sure, I -- I guess

06:41.836 --> 06:44.099
I could cancel my suite
at the Four Seasons...

06:44.229 --> 06:47.581
and
my expensive prostitute.

06:47.711 --> 06:49.931
♪♪

06:50.061 --> 06:50.932
[types on keyboard]

06:51.062 --> 06:52.716
[rumbling]

06:56.720 --> 06:59.157
Can you believe these
little drills are optional?

06:59.288 --> 07:02.422
If I didn't have a little drill,I'd kill myself like Klaus.

07:02.552 --> 07:04.424
I'm assuming
it was a suicide?

07:04.554 --> 07:06.295
Do we know? Do we care?

07:06.426 --> 07:08.297
-I don't know.
The woman who called Douglas --

07:08.428 --> 07:09.864
-Douglas?
-My jerk-off robot --

07:09.994 --> 07:11.518
-Your what?
-My regularrobot!

07:13.389 --> 07:15.696
The woman who called Douglas
was light on details...

07:15.826 --> 07:17.437
of Klaus's death.

07:17.567 --> 07:19.526
Which is the topic
of this conversation.

07:19.656 --> 07:21.528
Master, you seem tense.

07:21.658 --> 07:23.747
Would you like
to jerk me off?

07:23.878 --> 07:26.707
Wait. You do him?

07:28.360 --> 07:30.101
[sing-songy]
Awkward.

07:32.930 --> 07:36.238
♪♪

07:36.368 --> 07:39.546
Thank you all for coming
on such short notice.

07:39.676 --> 07:41.461
I'm Sister Madeline.

07:41.591 --> 07:45.682
I met Klaus while passing out
food and blankets on Skid Row.

07:45.813 --> 07:47.336
Excuse me, Stan Smith.

07:47.467 --> 07:48.946
I'd like to start
by saying I was invited

07:49.077 --> 07:50.600
so I'm allowed
to be here.

07:50.731 --> 07:52.733
Now, where are you passing out
these free blankets?

07:53.908 --> 07:57.389
I was with Klaus
in his final moments.

07:57.520 --> 07:59.566
He requested that I
gather you all together

07:59.696 --> 08:02.960
and show you this video.

08:03.091 --> 08:05.833
Dearest Smiths...
[coughs]

08:05.963 --> 08:08.226
...I bet you always wondered
what happened

08:08.357 --> 08:10.141
-to good, ol' Klaus.
-Nope.

08:10.272 --> 08:12.579
-Not me.
-Oh, thatKlaus!

08:12.709 --> 08:17.714
Well, [coughs] after I left,
my life went downhill.

08:17.845 --> 08:21.152
I caught Hep C from a plum
at the 99 cent store.

08:21.283 --> 08:25.069
And because I didn't have
insurance, I joined the army,

08:25.200 --> 08:27.550
but they sent me directly
to the Moon Wars

08:27.681 --> 08:29.596
where I went
completely insane

08:29.726 --> 08:32.729
after my brain was infested
with moon mites.

08:32.860 --> 08:34.470
[coughs]

08:34.601 --> 08:36.994
But I never blamed you guys.

08:37.125 --> 08:40.171
You were the only family...

08:40.302 --> 08:42.609
I ever loved.

08:42.739 --> 08:45.046
[coughs]

08:48.397 --> 08:49.833
Was that a snuff film?

08:49.964 --> 08:51.792
You should be ashamed
of yourselves!

08:51.922 --> 08:54.011
You all turned your back
on your friend,

08:54.142 --> 08:56.274
and he died alone.

08:56.405 --> 08:58.189
What do you want us to do
about it, lady?

08:58.320 --> 08:59.669
Give him
a proper funeral!

08:59.800 --> 09:01.541
Say some nice things!

09:01.671 --> 09:03.543
Throw in one of those blankets
you've been yapping about

09:03.673 --> 09:05.675
and we got a deal,
but I want it upfront.

09:05.806 --> 09:08.243
I've been burned before.

09:08.373 --> 09:10.114
Fine. We'll throw Klaus
a stupid funeral.

09:10.245 --> 09:13.770
-Then will you feel better?
-This isn't about me.

09:13.901 --> 09:16.033
-It's about Klaus!
-[door slams]

09:16.164 --> 09:18.645
Oh, but it isabout me.

09:18.775 --> 09:21.517
[voice deepening]
Andit's about Klaus,

09:21.648 --> 09:25.782
for I...am...Klaus!

09:25.913 --> 09:27.741
Sorry,
did you say something?

09:27.871 --> 09:29.656
[high-pitched voice] Oh,
just conversing with the Lord.

09:29.786 --> 09:31.571
He's the best, you know.

09:32.746 --> 09:34.269
Okay.

09:34.399 --> 09:35.792
Remember the blanket.

09:38.273 --> 09:39.317
[door slams]

09:41.537 --> 09:43.713
♪♪

09:43.844 --> 09:45.715
So everyone
has their assignments

09:45.846 --> 09:47.674
for Klaus's
funeral preparations.

09:47.804 --> 09:49.023
By the way,
where's Jeff?

09:49.153 --> 09:50.285
I sent him home
with the kids.

09:50.415 --> 09:51.852
He wasn't here
when we had Klaus.

09:51.982 --> 09:54.071
What?! Yes, he was!

09:54.202 --> 09:56.378
I'm...assuming...

09:56.508 --> 09:59.076
based on information available
to anybody.

09:59.207 --> 10:01.122
Come on,
let's get this over with.

10:01.252 --> 10:02.819
This isn't something
to "get over with."

10:02.950 --> 10:04.299
It's a chance
to come to terms

10:04.429 --> 10:07.389
with the great loss
you all must feel.

10:07.519 --> 10:08.564
Quick question --

10:08.695 --> 10:09.696
you're Klaus, right?

10:09.826 --> 10:11.698
What?!
Who's Klaus?!

10:11.828 --> 10:14.483
That's...
not what you'd say.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.659
[normal voice] Okay,
this family owes me an apology.

10:16.790 --> 10:19.314
They were wrong
to treat me so badly.

10:19.444 --> 10:22.796
-[menacing music plays]
-And once the sobering reality
of my funeral hits them,

10:22.926 --> 10:24.493
they'll sob,

10:24.624 --> 10:25.973
they'll wail,

10:26.103 --> 10:28.889
they'll beg the heavens
for my return!

10:29.019 --> 10:32.719
Huh. So it's a goof.
That's pretty cool!

10:32.849 --> 10:35.330
Oh, you know what would be agood way to reveal you're alive?

10:35.460 --> 10:36.723
When they're kneeling
in front of your casket,

10:36.853 --> 10:38.376
just, like,
fart really loud.

10:38.507 --> 10:40.596
[chuckles]
No, wait. That's too good.

10:40.727 --> 10:41.771
I want to do that.

10:41.902 --> 10:44.556
Oh, man, I am gonna be
the hit of the funeral!

10:44.687 --> 10:46.907
Us at Familyland.
Us at the beach.

10:47.037 --> 10:50.127
Oh, look.Remember when we ate this pasta?

10:50.258 --> 10:53.391
Oh, my God. Yes!
It was so good!

10:53.522 --> 10:54.784
I got full, though.

10:54.915 --> 10:57.787
Hey, I'm sorry
we lost touch.

10:57.918 --> 10:59.659
-What happened to us?
-I don't know.

10:59.789 --> 11:01.835
The pictures stop
after the pasta.

11:01.965 --> 11:03.837
[high-pitched voice]
How's it going down here?

11:03.967 --> 11:06.840
Have you found any good photos
of Klaus for the slideshow?

11:06.970 --> 11:08.537
Actually, it doesn't seem like
we have any.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.408
What?!
How is that possible?

11:10.539 --> 11:12.323
I guess we didn't have
an underwater camera.

11:12.454 --> 11:15.892
Jesus H., how stupid are you?
He lived in a bowl.

11:16.023 --> 11:18.373
You don't have to put the camera inthe bowl.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.767
Why do you have such a boner
for Klaus?

11:20.897 --> 11:21.942
Aren't you married to God?

11:22.072 --> 11:23.639
Just find a picture!

11:25.772 --> 11:27.687
Oh, here's one with Klaus
in the background.

11:27.817 --> 11:29.689
That's a tangerine.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.694
Eh. We'll just
draw some eyes on it.

11:34.824 --> 11:38.610
[scissors snipping]

11:38.741 --> 11:40.700
Stan,
what are you doing?

11:40.830 --> 11:43.920
Aren't -- Aren't they asparagus?[munching]

11:46.227 --> 11:48.620
God,
how are you even alive?

11:48.751 --> 11:50.927
Francine, I have to
come clean with you.

11:51.058 --> 11:54.148
I'm not doing
as well as I maybe look.

11:54.278 --> 11:55.802
You look like
you're dying.

11:55.932 --> 11:56.846
That's just a facade.

11:56.977 --> 11:59.414
My life's
not a fairy tale.

11:59.544 --> 12:00.763
This is a ferret tail.

12:00.894 --> 12:03.940
Nah, things aren't
that great for me either.

12:04.071 --> 12:07.378
I have to confess,
when I agreed to marry Toshi,

12:07.509 --> 12:09.685
I had him confused
with Snot.

12:09.816 --> 12:12.644
I feel like everything changed
for us after the divorce.

12:12.775 --> 12:14.385
People don't talk about
that part.

12:14.516 --> 12:15.735
What happened to us?

12:15.865 --> 12:18.738
When did everything become
a fight?

12:18.868 --> 12:21.088
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry about Klaus?!

12:21.218 --> 12:23.830
No, we're talking about
our marriage falling apart.

12:23.960 --> 12:25.179
Ever heard of it?

12:25.309 --> 12:26.963
Well, start talking
about Klaus

12:27.094 --> 12:29.313
or I'll tell God
you should all go to hell!

12:29.444 --> 12:31.054
Ever heard of that?

12:33.448 --> 12:36.625
[stammers] This robot
was trying to get fresh.

12:36.756 --> 12:38.801
[normally]
Can you believe this family?

12:38.932 --> 12:41.108
All they care about
is themselves.

12:41.238 --> 12:42.892
Wow, you sound like Klaus!

12:43.023 --> 12:44.676
[stammers] I am Klaus!

12:44.807 --> 12:46.200
Oh, yeah.
Oh, oh, you got that plan.

12:46.330 --> 12:47.984
You're going to fart
or something at a funeral?

12:48.115 --> 12:48.898
Ugh. That's so stupid.

12:49.029 --> 12:50.465
That was your idea!

12:50.595 --> 12:52.684
Well, I see
how it could work.

12:52.815 --> 12:54.861
I guess it would all depend
on the execution.

12:54.991 --> 12:56.340
Well, good luck
at the wedding.

12:59.082 --> 13:03.434
♪♪

13:03.565 --> 13:04.784
[slowly]
♪ Hey, now♪

13:04.914 --> 13:06.133
♪ You're an all-star♪

13:06.263 --> 13:07.917
♪ Get your game on♪

13:08.048 --> 13:09.832
♪ Go, play♪

13:09.963 --> 13:11.268
♪ Hey now♪

13:11.399 --> 13:12.748
♪ You're a rock star♪

13:12.879 --> 13:14.097
♪ Get the show on♪

13:14.228 --> 13:15.795
♪ Get paid♪

13:15.925 --> 13:19.711
♪ And all that glitters
is gold♪

13:19.842 --> 13:25.369
♪ Only shooting stars
break the mold♪

13:28.024 --> 13:30.897
[high-pitched voice]
Klaus was a special fish

13:31.027 --> 13:34.030
who swam his way
into our hearts.

13:34.161 --> 13:37.381
Perhaps someone would like
to say a few words?

13:37.512 --> 13:38.774
Stan?

13:41.472 --> 13:42.822
Uh, okay.

13:42.952 --> 13:44.780
Uh, Klaus.

13:44.911 --> 13:46.826
Well, he was a fish.
We know that.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.698
And he lived in our house
for a few weeks.

13:49.829 --> 13:51.047
For years!

13:51.178 --> 13:54.485
Maybe focus
on your emotions.

13:54.616 --> 13:57.924
Like crippling guilt
or haunting remorse?

13:59.316 --> 14:00.840
[cries]

14:00.970 --> 14:03.581
Yes, it's okay to cry.

14:03.712 --> 14:05.845
Let it flow.

14:05.975 --> 14:08.282
[laughing] I'm sorry.
I'm not crying, I'm laughing.

14:08.412 --> 14:10.937
I'm just remembering this time
Klaus tried to convince us

14:11.067 --> 14:12.939
he could kick a football
over a Burger King.

14:13.069 --> 14:15.332
Ha!
He was such a liar.

14:15.463 --> 14:17.030
Remember when he told us

14:17.160 --> 14:19.728
he beat up Brett Favre
at a mini-golf course?

14:19.859 --> 14:21.948
-FRANCINE: What an idiot!
-[laughter]

14:22.078 --> 14:23.427
Check this out, guys.

14:23.558 --> 14:26.517
I always said Klaus
was a wiener.

14:26.648 --> 14:30.086
[normally] Shut up!
Shut up!

14:30.217 --> 14:32.001
You guys are ruining
my funeral!

14:32.132 --> 14:33.960
Whoa, you do a better Klaus
than he did.

14:34.090 --> 14:35.570
I amKlaus!

14:35.700 --> 14:37.224
Klaus, now's the time
for the fart.

14:37.354 --> 14:38.703
Shut up.

14:39.052 --> 14:42.620
I gave you all every chance to
say one decent thing about me.

14:42.751 --> 14:47.364
Now I'll give you
one final chance.

14:47.495 --> 14:49.062
Did you kill a nun?

14:49.192 --> 14:51.107
That's it!

14:51.238 --> 14:53.980
Whoa, this is gonna be
some fart.

14:54.110 --> 14:56.330
[can hissing]

14:56.460 --> 14:58.027
ROGER: Wowee.

14:58.158 --> 14:59.550
[multiple thuds]

15:02.031 --> 15:03.903
STEVE:
What -- What's going on?

15:04.033 --> 15:06.470
FRANCINE: Where are we?

15:11.998 --> 15:13.956
We're...underwater.

15:14.087 --> 15:16.045
And we're in the attic.

15:16.176 --> 15:18.787
Oh, crap.
We're in Klaus's bowl.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.658
No, it's worse.

15:20.789 --> 15:22.660
We're in Klaus's body.

15:22.791 --> 15:26.229
KLAUS: Bingo, jerkwads.

15:26.360 --> 15:28.101
Welcome to hell,

15:28.231 --> 15:30.364
otherwise known as my life.

15:30.494 --> 15:32.105
ROGER: Oh, my God.

15:32.235 --> 15:33.715
I left my charger
out there

15:33.845 --> 15:35.412
and my phone's at 4%!

15:35.543 --> 15:37.893
This isgonna suck!

15:40.287 --> 15:42.463
♪♪

15:42.593 --> 15:44.508
STEVE: Klaus, what the hell
is going on?

15:44.639 --> 15:47.511
You shrunk us down and put us
in a fish-sized submarine?

15:47.642 --> 15:49.035
Don't be stupid, Steve.

15:49.165 --> 15:51.037
Even science
has its limits.

15:51.167 --> 15:54.083
I simply transferred all of yourconsciousnesses into my body,

15:54.214 --> 15:56.607
so you'd feel
what it's like to be me.

15:56.738 --> 15:57.739
No more questions!

15:57.869 --> 16:00.089
Wait, why did you
put yourself in here?

16:00.220 --> 16:01.482
Great question.

16:01.612 --> 16:03.484
That was a mistake.

16:03.614 --> 16:05.051
Okay, quick poll.

16:05.181 --> 16:07.314
Who wants to learn
Klaus's dumb lesson?

16:07.444 --> 16:09.098
Not me.
I want to watch TV.

16:09.229 --> 16:10.317
We've got to
find someone

16:10.447 --> 16:12.101
to help us
get back into our bodies.

16:12.232 --> 16:15.757
Maybe we can use these controls
to call for help.

16:15.887 --> 16:17.237
Blat! Eep! Ooh!

16:17.367 --> 16:18.281
You don't know
what you're doing.

16:18.412 --> 16:19.935
Use one of the presets.

16:20.066 --> 16:22.285
Wuzzuuuuuuuup!

16:22.416 --> 16:24.679
[imitating Borat] My wife!

16:24.809 --> 16:26.942
[normally] It's five to watch,
ten to touch.

16:28.117 --> 16:29.858
I -- I used to work
at a movie theater

16:29.989 --> 16:32.208
where it cost extra
to touch the screen.

16:32.339 --> 16:34.645
Eh, you clowns,
get out of the way.

16:34.776 --> 16:37.300
There's his cup.
That's how he gets around.

16:37.431 --> 16:38.693
[console beeps]

16:38.823 --> 16:40.216
[water sloshes]

16:40.347 --> 16:41.478
Nice move, Francine.

16:41.609 --> 16:43.524
It's obviously the levers.

16:45.700 --> 16:48.572
Yeah!
Daddy just dunked on y'all!

16:50.792 --> 16:52.011
Stan!

16:52.141 --> 16:55.188
♪♪

16:55.318 --> 16:56.885
Who lit
a Yankee candle?

16:57.016 --> 16:58.278
I like
the smell of cookies,

16:58.408 --> 17:00.106
but I don't have
the time to bake.

17:00.236 --> 17:02.978
Klaus, you've got to help us.
We're all gonna die.

17:03.109 --> 17:05.285
[scoffs]
I don't care if I die.

17:05.415 --> 17:08.331
In fact,
welcome to my suicide.

17:08.462 --> 17:10.899
[laughs maniacally]

17:11.030 --> 17:12.031
[console beeping]

17:12.161 --> 17:14.294
[vocalizing]

17:14.424 --> 17:19.777
♪♪

17:19.908 --> 17:21.388
STAN: That was lucky.

17:21.518 --> 17:23.390
Now we just have to
make it to the front door.

17:25.261 --> 17:27.350
[grunting]

17:27.481 --> 17:31.180
♪♪

17:31.311 --> 17:34.227
Oh, thank God. Jeff forgot
one of our kids again.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.404
It's...Noah.

17:37.534 --> 17:42.235
[lisping] Fishy, your skeleton
needs to come out.

17:42.365 --> 17:44.280
The little creep's
gonna taxidermy us.

17:44.411 --> 17:46.413
-Go for his knees.
-No, dummy. Choke him.

17:46.543 --> 17:48.154
You idiots,
kick him in the balls.

17:48.284 --> 17:50.634
We should be kicking Klaus
in the balls.

17:50.765 --> 17:53.333
You can't kick Klaus
in something he doesn't have.

17:53.463 --> 17:54.943
[laughter]

17:55.074 --> 17:56.553
Good burn, son.

17:56.684 --> 17:59.208
-Hayley, you got one?
-There's a peanut on the floor.

17:59.339 --> 18:00.644
Hmm, kind of a thinker.

18:00.775 --> 18:01.645
I obviously get it,

18:01.776 --> 18:03.082
but what about
the broader audience

18:03.212 --> 18:04.213
you want to reach
with your comedy?

18:04.344 --> 18:06.389
No, there's a peanut
on the floor.

18:06.520 --> 18:07.869
Noah's allergic.

18:07.999 --> 18:10.089
If you have to explain it,
Hayley, it's not funny.

18:10.219 --> 18:13.179
No, we flick the peanut
in Noah's mouth!

18:13.309 --> 18:18.271
♪♪

18:18.401 --> 18:20.273
Fish--
[gags]

18:21.665 --> 18:25.104
[coughs]
I got to get my EpiPen!

18:25.234 --> 18:26.453
ALL: Yes!

18:26.583 --> 18:29.369
Wait. Do you guys realize
what's happening?

18:29.499 --> 18:31.893
When we all
make fun of Klaus,

18:32.023 --> 18:34.417
we get along,
like at his funeral!

18:34.548 --> 18:38.378
That must be why everything
fell apart after he left.

18:38.508 --> 18:41.990
Klaus is the glue that
holds this family together!

18:42.121 --> 18:44.340
Klaus is
incredibly important...

18:44.471 --> 18:47.082
because
he sucks so much.

18:47.213 --> 18:49.040
-[gentle music plays]
-Thank you.

18:49.171 --> 18:50.825
That's all I wanted.

18:50.955 --> 18:54.785
I just needed to be appreciated
for something.

18:54.916 --> 18:56.657
-[picture clatters]
-Great, great.

18:56.787 --> 18:58.398
We all love each other again.
Now down the stairs.

18:58.528 --> 19:03.142
♪♪

19:03.316 --> 19:07.711
♪♪

19:07.842 --> 19:09.931
Klaus,
where's your door claw?!

19:10.061 --> 19:11.150
I buried it.

19:11.280 --> 19:12.586
It's what
I bludgeoned the nun with

19:12.716 --> 19:14.283
before I stole her body.

19:14.414 --> 19:16.938
Steve, tell your robot
to open the door.

19:17.068 --> 19:19.114
I can't.
See his eyes?

19:19.245 --> 19:22.465
It's been over 24 hours
since I serviced him.

19:22.596 --> 19:24.337
-What?
-[sighs]

19:24.467 --> 19:26.948
Okay, it's not a regular robot.
It's a pleasure bot.

19:27.078 --> 19:29.385
And there's only one way to
get him out of attack mode --

19:29.516 --> 19:30.821
pleasure him.

19:30.952 --> 19:32.171
Oh, God.

19:32.301 --> 19:33.259
Don't worry.

19:33.389 --> 19:35.261
Together, we can do this.

19:35.391 --> 19:38.177
To battle stations!

19:38.307 --> 19:42.355
♪♪

19:42.485 --> 19:43.747
Follow my lead!

19:43.878 --> 19:45.619
I know what he likes.

19:45.749 --> 19:47.229
[consoles beeping]

19:47.360 --> 19:52.060
♪♪

19:52.191 --> 19:56.673
♪♪

19:56.804 --> 20:00.329
[mechanical moaning]

20:00.460 --> 20:03.724
[sighs happily]

20:05.856 --> 20:08.163
♪♪

20:08.294 --> 20:09.382
HAYLEY: We made it.

20:09.512 --> 20:11.297
Well, let me take the helm,

20:11.427 --> 20:13.777
and we'll get you back
in your bodies.

20:13.908 --> 20:15.910
I want to
go find Toshi first.

20:16.040 --> 20:18.434
After all this,
you still want to be with him?

20:18.565 --> 20:20.697
No, I just think
it will be easier

20:20.828 --> 20:22.917
to break up with him
inside the fish.

20:23.047 --> 20:25.311
-You mean it, honey?
-Come here you.

20:25.441 --> 20:31.926
♪♪

20:32.056 --> 20:35.408
Well, my company was surprised
I moved it to Langley Falls,

20:35.538 --> 20:38.280
but I had to oversee
a very important merger.

20:38.411 --> 20:41.109
To Mom and Dad's
second marriage!

20:41.240 --> 20:43.111
[glasses clink]

20:43.242 --> 20:46.941
Ahem. Guys, it's great
to be back with the family,

20:47.071 --> 20:48.769
and I'd like to say...

20:48.899 --> 20:51.511
[chanting]
Disposal. Disposal.

20:51.641 --> 20:55.210
ALL: [chanting] Disposal!
Disposal! Disposal!

20:55.341 --> 20:56.559
Disposal!

20:58.387 --> 21:01.172
I'm the glue, baby!

21:01.303 --> 21:02.391
[disposal whirring]

21:02.522 --> 21:04.393
Bye bye! See you soon!

21:06.482 --> 21:08.223
--Captions by VITAC--
